title: debuginfo dies on librustdoc

labels.name: A-debuginfo
labels.description: Area: Debugging information in compiled programs (DWARF, PDB, etc.)

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

body:
`rustc -Z [extra-]debug-info src/librustdoc/lib.rs` ICEs with:

```
task 'rustc' failed at 'index out of bounds: the len is 0 but the index is 0', /home/cmr/hacking/rust2/src/libsyntax/codemap.rs:452
error: internal compiler error: unexpected failure
This message reflects a bug in the Rust compiler. 
We would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/mozilla/rust/wiki/HOWTO-submit-a-Rust-bug-report
note: the compiler hit an unexpected failure path. this is a bug
note: try running with RUST_LOG=rustc=1 to get further details and report the results to github.com/mozilla/rust/issues
task '<main>' failed at 'explicit failure', /home/cmr/hacking/rust2/src/librustc/lib.rs:440
```
